Fettucine with Steak and Avocado Sauce

8 oz whole grain fettucine
1 avocado, peeled and pitted
1 tbsp fresh lime juice
1/4 c greek yogurt
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 lb loin beef, trimmed of fat and cut into 1/2" strips
4 cloves garlic, chopped
2 roma tomatoes, chopped
1/4 c minced fresh cilantro (optional garnish)

Cook fettucine al dente according to package directions. Drain and set aside.

In a large bowl, mash avodaco using a fork until smooth. Stir in lime juice, yogurt, and salt. Set aside. In a large non-stick skillet on medium, add beef and saute for 2 min. Add garlic and cook for 5 more minutes, or until strips are cooked through, turning occasionally. Drain beef and garlic in a fine mesh strainer, then transfer to avocado mixture. Add fettucini and toss. When serving, garnish with tomatoes and cilantro.


Nutrition:
Serves: 4 |  Serving Size: 2 cups

Per serving: Calories: 367; Total Fat: 9g; Saturated Fat: 2g; Monounsaturated Fat: 4g; Cholesterol: 33mg; Sodium: 177mg; Carbohydrate: 49g; Dietary Fiber: 10g; Sugar: 3g; Protein: 24g

Nutrition Bonus: Potassium: 476mg; Iron: 27%; Vitamin A: 11%; Vitamin C: 29%; Calcium: 5% 

